@page "/"

<PageTitle>Loan Portal</PageTitle>

<h1>Loan Portal</h1>

<p>
    Blazor <strong>Server</strong> website with <strong>ASP.NET Core Identity</strong> for login and roles.
    Loan data is stored in <strong>SQL Server</strong> and accessed with <strong>Dapper</strong>.
</p>

<div class="card mb-3">
    <div class="card-body">
        <h5 class="card-title">Demo logins (seeded on first run)</h5>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Officer:</strong> officer@bank.com / Officer@123 — can approve pending loans</li>
            <li><strong>Customer:</strong> alice@example.com / Customer@123 — sees own loans and pays</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mb-0 text-muted">Use Account → Login, then open the Loans page.</p>
    </div>
</div>

<p>
    <a class="btn btn-primary" href="loans">Go to Loans</a>
    <a class="btn btn-outline-secondary ms-2" href="Account/Login">Login</a>
</p>
